This paper deals with privacy-preserving data analysis, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a protocol for identifying heavy hitters, which involves analyzing large datasets, making it relevant to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves analyzing the utility of the proposed protocol, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT).
